18/04/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The BiH Election Commission made several decisions about the upcoming 2 October municipal elections on Friday (16 April).
Timetables were set for political parties and candidates to confirm their participation, for municipal election commissions to draw up lists of eligible voters, for citizens to register to vote, for the final lists of candidates to be drawn up, and for results to be announced.
In other news, a Bosniak who came under suspicion of being linked to the 11 March Madrid terror bombings surrendered voluntarily to the Spanish police on Friday, BiH Foreign Ministry officials said.Mostar-born Sanel Sjekirica, 24, has denied involvement.(Dnevni avaz, RTRS, NTV Hayat, PBS BiH - 17/04/04)
